<!DOCTYPE html> <html lang="en" dir="ltr"> <head> <meta charset="utf-8"> <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" /> <title>Doug Hamaker | The UX Designer's Responsibility</title> <meta name="description" content="We're creating the public marketplaces, social clubs, and business settings for the 21st century."> <!-- Global site tag (gtag.js) - Google Analytics --> <script async src="https://www.googletagmanager.com/gtag/js?id=UA-67028251-2"></script> <script> window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || []; function gtag(){dataLayer.push(arguments);} gtag('js', new Date()); gtag('config', 'UA-67028251-2'); </script> <link rel="stylesheet" href="../css/portfolio.css"> <!-- Fav and touch icons --> <!--<link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" sizes="144x144" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-144-precomposed.png"> <link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" sizes="114x114" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-114-precomposed.png"> <link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" sizes="72x72" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-72-precomposed.png"> <link rel="apple-touch-icon-precomposed" href="../assets/ico/apple-touch-icon-57-precomposed.png">--> <link rel="shortcut icon" href="../favicon.ico"> </head> <body> <header class="vcard"> <a href="../index.html"> <p class="fn">Doug Hamaker <span class="category"><abbr title="User Experience">UX</abbr></span></p> </a> </header> <main> <article class="blog"> <header> <a class="breadcrumb" href="../blog/index.html">Blog</a> <h1> The UX Designer&apos;s Responsibility </h1> </header> <p>UX design is a privilege and trust. We create online spaces and experiences: the public marketplaces, social clubs, and business settings for the 21st century.</p> <h2>Public Trust</h2> <p>We have an obligation to the Public. Our work should build trust in products and the Internet. It should satisfy consumer needs, make positive impressions, and be inclusive. It should seem easy and intuitive. Our solutions must be stable, flexible, and inter-operable. And, they need to be accessible by anyone, anywhere, anytime.</p> <h2>Business Trust</h2> <p>We have an obligation to product owners. Our strategies should produce products that are cost effective and easy to own. Our designs should not add to business risk. They should realize business strategies. And, they should produce long-term assets planned for compatibility with tomorrowâ€™s trends.</p> <h2>Professional Trust</h2> <p>We have an obligation to our profession. We work in an area of rapid change. We must remain curious, question, investigate, listen, and test our ideas. We must exercise our creativity and seek everywhere for sources of inspiration and learning. And, we must share our knowledge of practice, standards, and legislation with other designers and educate our colleagues from other fields.</p> </article> </main> <nav> <details> <summary><span>Site Menu<span></summary> <a href="../index.html">Home</a> <a href="../blog/index.html">Blog</a> <a href="../portfolio/index.html">Portfolio</a> <a href="../resume.html">Resume</a> <a href="../index-all.html">Index</a> </details> </nav> <footer>&copy;2018. Doug Hamaker <a rel="external" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/doug-hamaker-ux/" title="Visit LinkedIn Profile" target="_blank"> <img class="socialbutton" srcset=" ../i/In-2C-44px-TM.png, ../i/In-2C-94px-TM.png 1.5x, ../i/In-2C-128px-TM.png 2x " src="../i/In-2C-28px-TM.png" alt="LinkedIn Profile" > </a> <nav> <a href="../resume.html">Resume</a> <a href="../portfolio/index.html">Portfolio</a> <a href="../blog/index.html">Blog</a> <a href="../contact.html">Contact</a> <a href="../privacy.html">Privacy</a> </nav> </footer> </body> </html>